        <div class="col-8">
            A string is called a special string if it consists only of lowercase letters a and b and there is at least one b between two aâ€™s in the string . You are given the length n of the string and your task is to find the number of special strings of length n. Since the number of strings may be very large, therefore print it modulo 10^9+7.
<br><br><b>
            Input Format:
        </b><br> The first and only line of input contains n, denoting the length of the string.
<br><br><b>
            Output Format:
        </b><br> Output a single integer denoting the number of special strings of length n modulo 10^9+7.
<br><br><b>
            Constraints:
        </b><br> 1<=N<=10^7
<br><br><b>
            Sample Input:
        </b><br> 4
<br><br><b>
            Sample Output:
        </b><br> 8
<br><br><b>
            Sample Explanation:
        </b><br> The special strings of length 4 are : <br>abab<br>abba<br>abbb<br>baba<br>babb<br>bbab<br>bbba<br>bbbb
<br>
